    <statement><p>Simplify this expression.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{yr-y^{2}r^{2}}{y^{2}r^{2}-2yr+1}}=}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{yr}{yr-1}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To simplify the expression, we first factor both the numerator and denominator, and then cross out common terms:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{yr-y^{2}r^{2}}{y^{2}r^{2}-2yr+1}} \amp = \frac{{yr\mathopen{}\left(1-yr\right)}}{{\left(yr-1\right)\mathopen{}\left(yr-1\right)}} \\
                     \amp = \frac{{-yr\mathopen{}\left(yr-1\right)}}{{\left(yr-1\right)\mathopen{}\left(yr-1\right)}} \\
                     \amp = {-\frac{yr}{yr-1}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
</solution>
